### Foreign relations

Here's [Vladimir Putin](/Vladimir_Putin) and [Fidel Castro](/Fidel_Castro) in 2000. A picture that speaks volumes about enduring alliances, wouldn't you agree?

The [foreign policy](/Foreign_relations_of_Cuba) of [Cuba](/Cuba) underwent a significant recalibration and reduction in scope following the severe [economic hardship](/Economy_of_Cuba) that ensued from the abrupt collapse of the [Soviet bloc](/Soviet_bloc). Deprived of the massive Soviet subsidies and its primary [trading](/Trade) partner, [Cuba](/Cuba) found itself in a state of comparative international isolation throughout the 1990s. However, the island nation has since managed to forge and deepen bilateral cooperation agreements with several South American countries, most notably with [Venezuela](/Venezuela) and [Bolivia](/Bolivia), seeking new economic and political anchors. Presently, [Cuba](/Cuba) maintains normal diplomatic and economic relations with every country in the Western Hemisphere, with the singular, glaring exception of the [United States](/United_States).

The [United States](/United_States) continues to enforce an economic [embargo against Cuba](/United_States_embargo_against_Cuba), a policy that it justifies by stating it will remain in place "so long as [Cuba] continues to refuse to move toward democratization and greater respect for human rights." A rather convenient justification, depending on your perspective. The [European Union](/European_Union), while acknowledging and often criticizing [Cuba](/Cuba) for its "continuing flagrant violation of human rights and fundamental freedoms," simultaneously "reiterates its condemnation of the US embargo on [Cuba](/Cuba), and calls for it to be lifted forthwith, as the UN General Assembly has repeatedly demanded." A diplomatic tightrope walk, if ever there was one.

Beyond its immediate neighbors, [Cuba](/Cuba) has cultivated an increasingly robust relationship with the [People's Republic of China](/People%27s_Republic_of_China) and, perhaps predictably, with [Russia](/Russia), rekindling old ties. In total, [Cuba](/Cuba) maintains formal diplomatic relations with 160 nations worldwide. Furthermore, it has notably provided civilian assistance workers – primarily medical professionals – in more than 20 countries, a form of soft power projection that has garnered both praise and scrutiny. This international engagement stands in contrast to the reality of more than [two million exiles](/Cuban_exiles) who have departed the island for foreign countries over the decades, a persistent demographic truth. The current [Minister of Foreign Affairs](/Minister_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Cuba)) for [Cuba](/Cuba) is [Bruno Rodríguez Parrilla](/Bruno_Rodr%C3%ADguez_Parrilla).

